      "review_summary": "The PR makes Telegram isolated-ingress replay wait for deferred buffered processing, preserves retryable failed updates, rolls back committed dispatch dedupe state, and adds a public persistent-dedupe deletion operation.\n\nPR surface: Source +607, Tests +748, Generated 0. Total +1355 across 18 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. A retryable buffered dispatch failure reproduces the retained-spool path, and injecting persisted dedupe deletion failure exercises the dead-letter safeguard; the PR also supplies live after-fix state output.",
